title: England 19-16 France: Ben Te'o try seals opening victory | Daily Mail Online
text: show ad England 19-16 France: Ben Te'o try on Six Nations debut seals victory for the Red Rose at Twickenham England got their Six Nations campaign off to a winning start at Twickenham with a 19-16 victory over France France opened proceedings with a Camille Lopez penalty, one of three for the 27-year-old fly-half Owen Farrell was on target for the Red Rose, tucking away three penalties of his own France registered the game's first try on 59 minutes when Rabah Slimani forced himself over the line England struck back 10 minutes later when Ben Te'o scored a try on his Six Nations debut Farrell converted to put England ahead, heading into the final ten minutes of the encounter England have now won their 14th successive game under Eddie Jones and a record 15 in total Published: 18:40 GMT, 4 February 2017 | Updated: 18:58 GMT, 4 February 2017 102 shares
